Detailed Description

The expand route request.

After the normal header this packet contains (subType = EXPAND_ROUTE_REQUEST): Table begins at REQUEST_HEADER_SIZE.
PosSizeComment
0 2 bytes Number of items in the request
2 1 bit The start (origin) heading, in terms of towards node 0 or 1 ( 1 == node 0 ) (bit index 7).
2.125 1 bit The end (destination) heading in terms of towards node 0 or 1 ( 1 == node 0 ) (bit index 6).
2.25 1 bit Set if the endOffset should be ignored and use all of the segment. This is due to that we don't know in which direction we are driving on the segment (bit index 5).
2.375 1 bit Set if we should ignore startOffset (bit index 4).
2.5 1 bit Set to 1, all names should be printed in the turndescriptions (bit index 3).
2.625 1 bit Set to 1 if you want to remove the street name in the route if you have an ahead-turn and the street changes name (bit index 2).
2.75 1 bit Set if we have an u-turn (bit index 1).
2.875 1 bit Set if the street names should be abbreviated (bit index 0).
3 1 byte Wanted route type.
4 1 byte States if landmarks should be inlcuded or not.
5 1 byte One byte padding.
6 2 bytes Two bytes padding.
8 4 bytes Start and end offset.
12 4 bytes The requested language.
16 2 bytes Ordinal number of the packet.
18 2 bytes Type of name wanted in reply.
20 4 bytes Last ID on preceding map (multimap expand).
24 4 bytes ID of preceding map (multimap expand).
28 4 bytes ID of the country of preceding map (multimap expand).
32 4 bytes Number of mapID 2 countryID
36 8 bytes each mapID and countryID pair.
36 + (Number of mapID 2 countryID) * (4 + 4) 4 bytes each Start of the itemID vector.

const char *  text

Add one disturbance to the packet.

Only use this when the whole route is in the packet.

If this is a detour splitID and/or mergeID is set to the nodes where the route detours/joins, if these points are on this map.

Parameters:
nodeID The node where the disturbance is located
splitID If not detour MAX_UINT32
distNodeID node of a detours disturbance. MAX_UINT32 if on another map.(same as nodeID if not detour)
mergeID If not detour MAX_UINT32
distID The ID of the disturbance
type The type of disturbance
text The disturbance text.

distID The ID of the disturbance

text The disturbance text.
Returns:
-1 if fail otherwise the next position in the packet.
